        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: gate stable releases on Windows companion assets",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- require stable release publish to receive an explicit `windows_node_tag` and candidate-approved `windows_node_installer_digests` map before any publish child runs\n- compare the live source release installer digests with the approved map, carry the pinned map unchanged through Windows promotion, and verify exact target companion assets plus exact checksum-manifest membership immediately before publishing the GitHub release draft\n- make direct Windows promotion/recovery reject stale or extra `OpenClawCompanion-*` target assets, while keeping the installer lists as the explicit future-MSIX extension point\n- update the release-candidate helper, release docs, and maintainer skill so canonical stable invocation sequences pass both the tag and approved digest map\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test test/scripts/release-candidate-checklist.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n  - passed: 2 files, 53 tests\n- `pnpm check:workflows`\n  - passed: zizmor and workflow interpolation checks\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n  - passed: 677 files\n- `pnpm format:check -- .agents/skills/release-openclaw-maintainer/SKILL.md .github/workflows/openclaw-release-publish.yml .github/workflows/windows-node-release.yml docs/ci.md docs/reference/RELEASING.md scripts/release-candidate-checklist.mjs test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/release-candidate-checklist.test.ts`\n  - passed\n- `git diff --check`\n  - passed\n- `node -e \"const fs=require('fs');const yaml=require('yaml');for (const f of ['.github/workflows/openclaw-release-publish.yml','.github/workflows/windows-node-release.yml']) { yaml.parse(fs.readFileSync(f,'utf8')); console.log('parsed '+f); }\"`\n  - parsed both changed workflows\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider blacksmith-testbox --shell --timing-json -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`\n  - passed: provider `blacksmith-testbox`, Testbox `tbx_01ktz44b6neac09c06v942c7tm`, GitHub Actions run `27449837177`, exit 0\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --type Standard_D4ads_v6 --shell --timing-json -- env OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 corepack pnpm check:changed`\n  - passed: provider `azure`, lease `cbx_67aa7dcc4b29`, run `run_28fa51dde647`, exit 0\n- native Windows PowerShell recovery-guard probe through Crabbox\n  - passed: provider `azure`, lease `cbx_6601e641f33b`, run `run_a81860329ed2`; exact stale-target filtering and stable/correction tag classification\n- direct jq checksum-manifest parser probes\n  - passed: the exact two-entry manifest parses; malformed and extra-blank-line manifests exit nonzero instead of silently dropping lines\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high --stream-engine-output`\n  - clean: no accepted/actionable findings; overall patch correct, confidence 0.90\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Stable OpenClaw GitHub publication can no longer proceed without an explicitly approved Windows-node installer identity, successful signed-asset promotion, and an exact current companion asset/checksum contract.\n\nReal environment tested: GitHub release APIs/download endpoints, Blacksmith Testbox, and an AWS native Windows Crabbox lease.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Read-only validation of `openclaw/openclaw-windows-node@v0.6.3`; latest OpenClaw release asset/download inspection; native Windows download, SHA-256, and `Get-AuthenticodeSignature` probe for both v0.6.3 installers; direct jq malformed-manifest probes; native Windows PowerShell recovery-guard probe; final current-head `pnpm check:changed` on Azure Crabbox.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- current stable `openclaw/openclaw@v2026.6.6` contains only `openclaw-2026.6.6-dependency-evidence.zip`; the x64 installer, arm64 installer, and checksum latest-download URLs each returned HTTP 404\n- source `openclaw/openclaw-windows-node@v0.6.3` is published/non-prerelease with:\n  - `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-x64.exe`: `sha256:595a78a223f771adbaead34d56b190f5be5f97222d7707f8013ff4cc81d26983`\n  - `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-arm64.exe`: `sha256:cb33a5f802f5790b2ac25bcb12cc3c6cc98ef5fa9fa8af5f0133f2b47cfcb88a`\n- AWS Windows Crabbox provider/lease/run: `aws` / `cbx_07d0e0962266` / `run_a3307ad2fca3`\n- both installers matched the pinned hashes and returned Authenticode status `Valid`\n- exact signer subject for both: `CN=OpenClaw Foundation, O=OpenClaw Foundation, L=Mill Valley, S=California, C=US`\n- signer thumbprint for both: `27878F3064C86E08F9D1AB3885D34C0821887A80`\n\nObserved result after fix: The stable flow has a continuous approved-identity chain from release-candidate evidence through parent prevalidation, child hash/signature verification, exact recovery inventory, and the final pre-undraft asset/manifest gate. Malformed manifest lines fail closed, and direct recovery rejects unexpected target companion assets before upload while deriving stable/correction policy from the target tag.\n\nWhat was not tested: The mutating Windows promotion workflow and release publication were intentionally not dispatched.",
